      </svg>
    </section>

    <!-- Section: Limits & Risks -->
    <section id="limits">
      <h2>Limits & risks — what to watch</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Model bias — test locally on your patient population before trusting outputs.</li>
        <li>Privacy — facial/body imaging needs strict consent and secure storage.</li>
        <li>Regulation & liability — decision-influencing tools require careful governance.</li>
        <li>Human factors — maintain manual-skill training and override rules.</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="muted">Policy/consent template: <a class="link" href="https://www.srinjoysaha.com/pre-op-guidelines">srinjoysaha.com/pre-op-guidelines</a></p>

      <svg class="svg-divider" viewBox="0 0 800 60" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
        <rect width="800" height="60" fill="#f6fffb"></rect>
        <g fill="#0a9d77" opacity="0.12"><rect x="30" y="14" width="240" height="32" rx="6"/><circle cx="320" cy="30" r="18"/><rect x="380" y="12" width="380" height="36" rx="8"/></g>
      </svg>
    </section>

    <!-- Section: Implementation checklist -->
    <section id="implement">
      <h2>Implementation checklist — phased playbook</h2>
      <h3>Phase 0 — Internal prep (0–4 wks)</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Appoint project lead + working group (surgery, nursing, IT, admin).</li>
        <li>Map workflow: consult → imaging → OR → post-op → billing.</li>
        <li>Define 3 KPIs (consult conversion, documentation time, unplanned post-op visits).</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Phase 1 — Low risk quick wins (4–12 wks)</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Deploy admin/NLP pilot (1–2 clinicians). Measure documentation time at 4 & 12 weeks.</li>
        <li>Implement remote photo triage pilot (3 months) with clear escalation protocol.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Phase 2 — Consultation & planning (8–16 wks)</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Lease or purchase 3D capture (VECTRA / 3dMD); standardize capture SOPs; add simulation in consults.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Phase 3 — Intra-op pilots (12–24 wks)</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Pilot blood-loss estimation (Triton); require backup procedures and consent.</li>
        <li>Trial remote proctoring / recording for QA (Proximie).</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Phase 4 — Evaluate & scale (24–52 wks)</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Assess KPIs, ROI, renegotiate contracts and scale successful pilots.</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="muted">Download a printable checklist: <a class="link" href="https://www.srinjoysaha.com/resources/ai-checklist.pdf">srinjoysaha.com/resources/ai-checklist.pdf</a></p>
    </section>

    <!-- Section: Vendors -->
    <section id="vendors">
      <h2>Vendor suggestions — quick shortlist</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>3D imaging:</strong> Canfield (VECTRA), 3dMD, Crisalix.</li>
        <li><strong>Blood-loss monitoring:</strong> Triton (Gauss/Stryker).</li>
        <li><strong>Wound triage:</strong> Swift Medical.</li>
        <li><strong>OR connectivity/training:</strong> Proximie.</li>
        <li><strong>Admin/NLP:</strong> Microsoft / Nuance (Dragon, Copilot).</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="muted">Vendor demos & pilot tips: <a class="link" href="https://www.srinjoysaha.com/contact">srinjoysaha.com/contact</a></p>
    </section>

    <!-- Section: Data governance & KPIs -->
    <section id="resources">
      <h2>Data governance & KPI tracking</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Consent: explicit image/data use and de-identification clauses.</li>
        <li>Encryption & storage: vendor HIPAA-equivalent, region-appropriate residency.</li>
        <li>Access logs & role-based controls; contractual breach notifications.</li>
        <li>Track KPIs: documentation time, consult conversion, unplanned visits, OR metrics.</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="muted">Full resource pack: <a class="link" href="https://www.srinjoysaha.com/ai-resources">srinjoysaha.com/ai-resources</a></p>

